The paper deals with the problem of selecting the most appropriate base station for a UAV to connect to in an urban environment. This involves using machine learning techniques to identify the best base station based on various environmental factors. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a supervised learning-based association scheme, which involves training a neural network to identify the most suitable base station. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with wireless communication and signal processing, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
